  <h1>üîê Web Application Penetration Testing ‚Äì OWASP Juice Shop</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üéØ Project Overview</h2>
    <p>This project involves a full-scale penetration test on <strong>OWASP Juice Shop</strong>, an intentionally vulnerable web application. The goal is to identify and exploit OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities and suggest remediations.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üß∞ Tools & Technologies</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Recon:</strong> Nmap, Subfinder, AMASS, FFUF, HTTPX, theHarvester</li>
      <li><strong>Scanning:</strong> Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP</li>
      <li><strong>Manual Testing:</strong> Parameter tampering, JWT abuse, SQLi payloads</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üö® Discovered Vulnerabilities</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>No</th>
          <th>Vulnerability</th>
          <th>Description / Impact</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1</td><td>Broken Access Control</td><td>Cart manipulation via BasketId override</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2</td><td>SQL Injection</td><td>Login bypass, DB manipulation</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3</td><td>XSS (Stored/DOM)</td><td>Session theft, DOM/UI manipulation</td></tr>
        <tr><td>4</td><td>CSRF</td><td>Forced user actions via crafted HTML</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td><td>Null Byte Injection</td><td>Access sensitive .md backup files</td></tr>
        <tr><td>6</td><td>SSTI</td><td>Remote code execution via template injection</td></tr>
        <tr><td>7</td><td>Password Reset Exploit</td><td>Unauthorized reset by removing <code>currentPassword</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td>8</td><td>XXE</td><td>File disclosure using malicious XML (<code>/etc/passwd</code>)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üîí Remediation Recommendations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Enforce strong input validation and output encoding</li>
      <li>Use parameterized queries</li>
      <li>Enable CSRF protection with tokens</li>
      <li>Disable public admin role creation</li>
      <li>Harden JWT sessions and use secure cookies</li>
      <li>Patch all known CVEs</li>
      <li>Apply Content Security Policy (CSP)</li>
      <li>Educate developers on secure coding practices</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>üìÅ Project Structure</h2>
